Tenders worth more than Sh200 billion have been lined up for youth, women and people with disabilities this year, Deputy President William Ruto has said. The DP, who was speaking in Wote, Makueni County, yesterday during National Youth Week celebrations, told young people to get out of bed, put on their boots, tighten their belts and roll up their sleeves for gainful work. ALSO READ:

